{
  "article_id": "OxnardDailyCourier1928",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "\""
      },
      {
        "text": "The Daughters of the American Revolution",
        "entity_key": "daughters",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " stand for national defense and try to offset the communistic and pacifist propaganda in "
      },
      {
        "text": "this country",
        "entity_key": "co_usa",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ",\" said "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Alfred Brosseau",
        "entity_key": "abr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Washington, D. C.",
        "entity_key": "ci_dc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", president general of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Daughters of the American Revolution",
        "entity_key": "daughters",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " at a luncheon held Saturday in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Biltmore",
        "entity_key": "biltmore",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " by the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "dar_sb",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "La Cumbre",
        "entity_key": "dar_lc",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Golden West",
        "entity_key": "dar_gw",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " chapters of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the D. A. R.",
        "entity_key": "daughters",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " \""
      },
      {
        "text": "Our navy",
        "entity_key": "mi_navy",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " is in a deplorable condition and although we do not want to exceed other nations in our navy program, we must at least equal theirs for our own national defense.\" "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Brosseau",
        "entity_key": "abr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " stated that she was cleaning up old snags during her administration, which include the raising of the million dollars for "
      },
      {
        "text": "Constitution hall",
        "entity_key": "consthall",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " [sic], the memorial to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Caroline Scott Harrison",
        "entity_key": "mharrison",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", first president general; the memorial to the four organizers of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the D. A. R.",
        "entity_key": "daughters",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and the student loan fund, which aids those young men and women who have such a desire for education that they will give their first earnings after graduation to repay their debt. The outstanding national need of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "D. A. R.",
        "entity_key": "daughters",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she said, is a hall which can accommodate the hundreds of delegates coming to the conventions in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Washington",
        "entity_key": "ci_dc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The new $1,000,000 proposed "
      },
      {
        "text": "Constitution hall",
        "entity_key": "consthall",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " [sic] will meet all the requirements. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Winfield B. Metcalf",
        "entity_key": "mmetclaf",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " announced that a tablet to the \""
      },
      {
        "text": "Lost Woman of San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ",\" will be unveiled by the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara chapter",
        "entity_key": "dar_sb",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " at 2 o'clock next Saturday afternoon in the garden of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Old Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". This will be the first public ceremony ever to be held in the garden of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Permission has been granted by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Father Augustine",
        "entity_key": "aug",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " in honor of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Brosseau",
        "entity_key": "abr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Golden West Chapter",
        "entity_key": "dar_gw",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ventura county",
        "entity_key": "co_ventura",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is among those invited to attend. More than 110 members were present at the luncheon including "
      },
      {
        "text": "Miss Walter B. Meyer",
        "entity_key": "mmeyer",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. James Cerny",
        "entity_key": "mcerny",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Oxnard",
        "entity_key": "ci_oxnard",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". At the speaker's table were the following past regents in addition to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Brosseau",
        "entity_key": "abr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Miss Ethel M. Moss",
        "entity_key": "emoss",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who presided: "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Arthur Garland",
        "entity_key": "mgarland",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Henry J. Finger",
        "entity_key": "mfinger",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Guy P. Sawyer",
        "entity_key": "msawyer",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Charles Kirk",
        "entity_key": "mkirk",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", Mrs. Winfield B. Metcalf, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Mark Bradley",
        "entity_key": "mbradley",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Clara E. Herbert",
        "entity_key": "mherbert",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. N. S. Kaime",
        "entity_key": "mkaime",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Fred Jackson",
        "entity_key": "mjackson",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Miss Elizabeth Mason",
        "entity_key": "emas",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", regent of "
      },
      {
        "text": "La Cumbre chapter",
        "entity_key": "dar_lc",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. O. H. Piper",
        "entity_key": "mpiper",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Golden West chapter",
        "entity_key": "dar_gw",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. William Paulton",
        "entity_key": "mpaulton",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. C. W. Wells",
        "entity_key": "mwells",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "also were at the table. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Meyer",
        "entity_key": "mmeyer",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " reported a charmingly appointed luncheon, pastel sweetpeas forming the floral decoration."
      }
    ]
  ]
}